  "texts": [
    "Pioneering use of sophisticated mathematical constructs, such as matrix calculus and principles akin to Bernoulli's and Lorentz transformations, to enhance the analytical capabilities of LLMs.The structure of this article is: Section 2 reviews the literature in three primary areas relevant to the integration of a PIL in the Mistral LLM for enhanced information retrieval accuracy.",
    "Section 3 outlines the methodology of integrating the PIL into the Mistral LLM.",
    "Section 4 details the experimental setup and dataset description.Section 5 presents the results and performance evaluations.",
    "Section 6 discusses the implications, strengths, limitations, and future research directions.",
    "Finally, Section 7 concludes the study, summarizing its main findings and contributions."
  ]
}